Articles.Content:
Okay, this is a weird one for me.  I've been running basically the same set of addons for the last 3 or 4 months.  All I've done is update the addons as needed through CKAN.  I ran a couple of updates without running KSP after to verify the changes were good.  Yesterday, I ran KSP and found that after going to the R&D screen I couldn't do anything else.  I ALT-F4'd out of the program and re-launched only to discover that the R&D screen was the only one I could go to and no other buildings would open.  Even from the KSC overview going to the Pause/Options screen and clicking Exit to Main Menu did nothing.  Trying to exit to main menu on the R&D screen doesn't work either.

Even worse - there's no error logs.  Period.

Edit - I was able to get into the Astronaut Complex and then pulling up the debug, I'm getting a NullReferenceException when I click the "Leave Facility" button.  Looking at the full debug log in game, it's not showing where this problem is being created, but at least that's another clue?

EDIT: I looked at what mods we had in common. Wasted a few hours testing one mod by one. Traced it down to Better Time Warp Continued - which I didn't think had been updated recently???  But sure enough by deleting that mod the bug goes away in both a new game and my old saved game.

Ya exact same error I'm getting... I have not changed anything on my game (just not played in a week) and today I get this. Full game resinstall did nothing. Full mod reinstall did nothing to fix this. Only thing that seemed to work is to wipe the folder, and just install a stock game with no mods at all. Adding even 1 mod seemed to bring this back for me. Hope someone has a solution.

2 hours ago, Atlas Gaming said:

Traced it down to Better Time Warp - which I didn't think had been updated recently???

Better Time Warp has been been adopted by @linuxgurugamer a while ago, it's now called Better Time Warp Continued, latest version is good for KSP 1.8.1, see here

As an alternative you could also use this mod, while not recompiled it works fine with 1.8.1, confirmed myself and the author confirmed it to me too

Better Time Warp has been been adopted by @linuxgurugamer a while ago, it's now called Better Time Warp Continued, latest version is good for KSP 1.8.1, see here

You misunderstood me... That is the one - linuxgurugamers - which is not working... previous update worked fine, but I guess the latest one a week ago is what ended up making the mod crash our games. Keep in mind this may only be the case 'in combination' with the other mods we use. But through long one by one testing getting rid of that mod is what allowed the game to go back to normal.

But in the end it turned out to be "Better Time Warp Continued" aka Better Time Warp
